{"id":"248831601_Construction_and_enumeration_of_regular_maps_on_the_torus","abstract":"A construction is given for all the regular maps of type {3, 6} on the torus, with vvertices, v being any integer > 0. We also find bounds for the number of those maps, in particular for the case in which the maps contain “normal” Hamiltonian circuits. Using duality, the results may be applied for the maps of type {6, 3} too.","authors":["Amos Altshuler"],"meta":["March 1973Discrete Mathematics 4(3):201-217","DOI:10.1016/S0012-365X(73)80002-0"],"references":["287183736_Regular_maps_on_an_anchor_ring","287183453_On_the_regular_polyhedra_of_analysis_situs","270194680_Generators_and_Relations_in_Discrete_Groups","268918441_Sur_les_polyedres_reguliers_de_l'Analysis_Situs","266210952_Geometric_Embedding_of_Complexes","264928274_Finite_graphs_and_networks_An_introduction_with_applications_Konecnye_grafy_i_seti_Ubersetzung_aus_dem_Englischen_von_V_N_Burkov_S_E_Loveckii_V_B_Sokolov_Herausgegeben_von_A_I_Teiman","242789382_Hamiltonian_circuits_in_some_maps_on_the_torus","229221813_Polyhedral_realization_in_R3_of_triangulations_of_the_torus_and_2-manifolds_in_cyclic_4-polytopes","42318569_Finite_Graphs_and_Networks_An_Introduction_with_Applications"]}